				\begin{document}$$\:{NBN}_{tp}$$\end{document}. We take advantage of the different NBN rollout dates across postcodes and measure our IV as the number of months since the NBN upgrade commenced in a postcode. The NBN rollout across each postcode happens in stages, with some areas within a postcode getting upgraded first. We use the time in months since the first sub-area in a postcode was connected to the NBN as our IV. Once an area in a postcode gets upgraded, the NBN connection is rolled out across other areas within the postcode over time. Intuitively, the date of first upgrade completion in a postcode sub-area will be correlated with the proportion or share of the entire postcode that gets upgraded over time. The proposed IV is therefore varying across time and postcode.
